==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Molybdenum
<hw>Mol`yb*de"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.: cf. F.
<ets>molybd⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>. See <er>Molybdena</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare element of the chromium group, occurring
in nature in the minerals molybdenite and wulfenite, and when reduced
obtained as a hard, silver-white, difficulty fusible metal. Symbol Mo.
Atomic number 42. Atomic weight 95.94.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Molybdic</ent>⟦br⟧
